<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Very convenient I have stayed here 4 times now, after the long intercontinental flights from Europe that get in late at night, it is simply great to just walk up the stairs from the international terminal and be in your bed 5 minutes after you exited passport  customs. Good: Rooms are quite spacious for an airport hotel. Not quite as big as comparably priced rooms downtown, but at least 3 times the size of something like the Miami International Airport Hotel, where the rooms are just exactly the size of your bed. Ample room to work and relax. The rooms have been recently refurbished and look nice and clean. The hotel now operates a highspeed WLAN (54MBit) but it is very expensive. If you are lucky you can catch a ride on one of the free WLANs that transmit from the various Premier Lounges at the terminal, in my room I was able to connect for free. Also very good is the excellent breakfast, lots of good Mexican dishes, choice of eggs and variety of cereals, fruits, bread and pastry.Bad: On some days of the year, the entire airport smells like a sewer (you'll notice it as soon as you land) and this bad smell then also enters the hotel and the rooms. Not the fault of the hotel, but simply a problem of the bad pollution in Mexico. Also, traffic into town is much much worse in the mornings than if you arrive late at night, so if your final destination is the city, you may want to consider going downtown right away.Finally, the terminal is currently (March 2005) undergoing major reconstruction, so there will be noises for the next months. Luckily the hotel tries to move all guests as far away as possible from the construction work, I had no problems in my room. 
